OL,3,CWatchdog calls for 'radical overhaul'
OL,4,Cof policing following TV documentary
OL,6,FIn a statement, they said: "The
OL,7,Fdocumentary laid bare how the
OL,8,FProfessional Standards Department and
OL,9,Feven the Independent Office of Police
OL,10,FConduct (IOPC) operate within systems
OL,11,Fand processes that result in decisions
OL,12,Fthat protect the police rather than
OL,13,Fthe public.
OL,15,F"This has serious implications for
OL,16,Fpolicing by consent which is the basic
OL,17,Ffoundation of British policing."
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G6/10
